description: Regular addition of the past tense suffix -ed to saw.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of saw

description: Nonstandard addition of -ed to saw, which is already a strong past tense form of see.

entries.meaning: (dialectal, often humorous) simple past tense of see
examples: "Yes, yes, el Pero! that was himself!" cried the captain; "I sawed him at the ale-house at Penzance with my own eye."
